碩士班應用語言學組碩士班應用語言學組課程暨升學/就職進路圖










 應用語言學組必修課程
研究方法與學術寫作 [Research Methods and Academic Writing]
學分數：3
時    數：3
This course has five major objectives. It aims to
(1) present an overview of the considerations involved in successful academic writing, 
(2) familiarize first-year graduate students with the style of English for academic purposes, 
(3) enhance students’ ability to write correct and fluent English, 
(4) introduce APA reference format, 
(5) introduce some research methods commonly used in Applied Linguistics.
【曾銘裕、徐淑瑛】




應用語言學組專業選修
 
1. 語言學理課程（三門選二門）
 句法學
[Syntax]
學分數：3
時    數：3
This class is designed to introduce generative grammar with special emphasis on building up students' analytic ability.  Students will be asked to read assigned materials analytically in order to be equipped with the ability to develop linguistic argumentations.  Students will be asked to read the assigned materials, be prepared for in class discussions and presentations. A final term paper is required. 
【徐淑瑛】
 
音韻學
[Phonology]
學分數：3
時　數：3
This course helps graduate students understand current theories of phonology, learn to analyze phonological data, and develop arguments for phonological analyses and descriptions. Therefore, they can contribute to the development of phonological theories itself or apply the knowledge to various studies in applied linguistics, e.g., L2 phonology development, teaching techniques and its interface with other grammatical components.
【歐淑珍】
 
語用學
[Pragmatics]
學分數：3
時    數：3
This course aims to offer an overview of the main topics of pragmatic studies and familiarize students with the basic methodology for pragmatic research and analysis through lectures by the instructor and students' participation in class activities and research project.
【曾銘裕】
 
 
2. 專業領域課程（三領域至少擇二領域各一門課修習）
 領域一：第二語言習得研究 
第二語言音韻習得
[Second Language Phonology Acquisition]
學分數：3
時    數：3
L2 phonological Acquisition is a complex process with several mixed factors such as learners' L1 phonological system, universal grammar and target language. These factors will be discussed by reading updated literatures looking into various L2 phonological levels (including segments and prosodic aspects). In the meanwhile, since perception plays an important role for learners' processing L2 input, factors constraining L2 speech perception will also be discussed.
【歐淑珍】
 
第二語言句法習得
[Second Language Syntax Acquisition]
學分數：3
時    數：3
This course discusses the main issues and current research on second language syntax studies from the Generative Grammar approach, and focuses on the second language syntax findings constrained by the theory of Universal Grammar. It also aims to provide the opportunity to critically evaluate theoretical models and hypotheses by applying them to the analysis of real data produced by second language learners
【徐淑瑛】
 
 領域二：語言與文化 
譬喻、認知與文化
[Metaphor, Cognition, and Culture]
學分數：3
時    數：3
Metaphor has long been considered a literary or rhetorical device, but recent studies have shown that metaphor is far more pervasive in daily communication than was assumed. This course has four objectives: (1) to introduce some of the key assumptions and hypotheses in cognitive approaches to language and communication, with a particular reference to metaphor studies; (2) to provide an overview of new developments in the studies of metaphor; (3) to outline the cognitive theory of metaphor; (4) to examine how the theory helps us understand the intricate relationship between language, mind, and culture.
【曾銘裕】
 
語言與社會
[Language and Society]
學分數：3
時    數：3
This course is intended to explore in great depth some of the concepts and methods used in sociolinguistics and linguistic anthropology. It aims to provide students with an overview of key developments in sociolinguistics and introduce them to various approaches to the study of language in its social context.
【曾銘裕】
 
言談分析
[Discourse Analysis]
學分數：3
時    數：3
This course has four major objectives. It aims to help students (1) understand the key concepts of discourse and discourse analysis, (2) develop the ability to describe clearly and analyze effectively the structures and processes of talks and texts, (3) raise their awareness of the linguistic construction of a variety of texts and text-types,  (4) help students develop a research method that can be used to answer various questions arising from discourse and text.
【曾銘裕】
  
領域三：外語教學與科技
英語教學研究
[Studies in English Language Teaching]
學分數：3
時    數：3
By the end of this course, students are expected to meet the following objectives:
(1) To demonstrate a general understanding of current trends in TESOL research context,
(2) To explain and analyze major concepts rooted Vygotsky's sociocultual theory and TESOL research framed in Vygotskian-inspired sociocultural perspectives,
(3) To develop a preliminary TESOL research proposal rooted in Vygotskian-inspired perspectives.
【楊鬱芬】
 
外語教學與科技：理論與實踐
 [Foreign Language Instruction and Technology: Theory and Practice]
學分數：3
時    數：3
The purpose of this course is to familiarize students with key concepts related to foreign language instruction and technology. With an emphasis on second language learning theories and teaching principles, it introduces eight optimal conditions for the designs of foreign language teaching tasks of technology use (internet; software, computer applications, online learning platforms, other technologies, etc). Students will take a part in various foreign language classrooms of technology use, observe/explore how these classrooms address second language learning theories and teaching principles, develop materials for to technology-enhance language classrooms and learn to develop their own lessons. Teacher behaviors, language learner behaviors and issues in these classrooms will be analyzed and discussed.
【楊鬱芬】
 
語言測驗 
[Language Testing]
學分數：3
時    數：3
This purpose of this course is threefold. First, it aims to help students gain a basic understanding of the fundamental concepts, principles, processes, and dilemmas of language testing and assessment. Second, it intends to develop in students the skills to plan, construct, and interpret results of language tests. Third, it seeks to equip students with the ability to write and speak clearly on language testing and assessment issues.
【施智閔、柯昭蓉】



創造力與外語教學：理論與實務 
[Creativity and Foreign Language Teaching: Theory and Practice]
學分數：3
時    數：3
This graduate seminar aims to provide graduate students interested in creativity with a thorough discussion on research in creativity and second language (L2) creativity, and to prepare them to do research in related areas. This course will first examine how creativity can be defined, assessed and trained. It will further discuss L2 creativity as the larger picture, with a specific focus on language play, humor, and creative pedagogy.
【系所教師】

 
 
3. 其他選修課程 
漢英比較句法
[Comparative Syntax of Chinese and English]
學分數：3
時     數：3
This course aims to discuss and familiarize students with several issues in the syntax of English and Mandarin Chinese. The discussion is mainly based on the framework of generative grammar, though related topics that are tackled in other frameworks, such as in functionalism and typology, will be discussed as well.  Students are asked to read assigned articles analytically and develop linguistic argumentations.  The topics covered include: Word order typology , Subject and Topic , Binding Theory (Anaphors, Pronouns, R-expressions) , Passives. Movement issues, and Relative clauses.
【徐淑瑛】
 
中英音韻對比分析
[Comparative Study of Chinese and English Phonology]
學分數：3
時     數：3
This course aims to familarize students with various phonological phenomena in English and Chinese, including their sound inventory, syllable structure, lexical prosody, metrical structure and intonation. The discussion is mainly based on the framework of generative grammar. The interaction of the two phonological systems will be introduced by reading papers concering code-switching, loanword and second language speech data. Students are required to conduct a mini-project and write a term paper to show their comprehension of the course materials and their ability of critical thinking and doing independent research.
【歐淑珍】
 
訊息結構研究
[Studies of Information Structure]
學分數：3
時    數：3
This course aims to study the syntax, semantics/pragmatics, and prosody of information structure from the perspectives of the generative grammar and functional (discourse) grammar. Issues include how the notions of topic and focus are represented in the formal and discourse grammars and what discrepancies exist between the given/new and the topic/focus dichotomies. It is hoped that with more focused discussion of these related issues students can develop their critical thinking and linguistic argumentation.
【徐淑瑛】
 
質性研究 
[Qualitative Research Methods]
學分數：3
時   數：3
This course introduces students to common qualitative research methods and techniques used in TESOL research. Students will explore practical and epistemological concerns in qualitative methods, qualitative data collection process and qualitative data analysis in the context of TESOL research. Guidance will be provided to help students carry out a small-scale qualitative research for a topic of interest in TESOL context.
【楊鬱芬】
 
應用語言學統計分析
[Statistical Applications in Applied Linguistics Research ]
學分數：3
時   數：3
This course is intended to quickly bring students to a practical, introductory understanding of the statistical techniques commonly employed in the field of applied linguistics and help them function as informed and intelligent consumers of the applied linguistics research with a quantitative orientation. The techniques to be covered as they pertain to applied linguistics research include related samples and independent samples t-tests, correlation, regression, chi-square test of association, and ANOVA.
【柯昭蓉】
 
語音學
[Phonetics]
學分數：3
時   數：3
This course aims at familiarizing students with advanced concepts in the field of phonetics, the study of speech sounds. The main content will include: (a) acoustic properties of segments (i.e., consonants and vowels) and suprasegments (i.e., pitch, duration and intensity), and (b) how the acoustic properties are perceived and processed in human language. It is expected that students will be able to apply the concepts and techniques in phonetics to various studies in applied linguistics, e.g., speech perception, experimental phonology, and the interface between phonetics and other grammatical components.
【歐淑珍】
 
數位學習與溝通
[Digital Literacies]
學分數：3
時   數：3
This course guides students to investigate digital literacy practices and communication that are carried out by second language learners. Historical backgrounds, perspectives, genres and discourse, and the study designs of digital literacy practices will be introduced. Students will critically evaluate current research literature in this field, discuss issues in the current literature, examine digital literacy instances, and conduct a small-scale empirical study for the related area of interest in digital literacy studies.
【楊鬱芬】




